 P(n) = \left\{\begin{aligned} &1 &&: n = 0\\ &P(n-1)+n^2 &&: n>0 \end{aligned} \right.
P(n) - P(n-1) = n^2 = 2{n \choose 2} + {n\choose 1}
{n \choose 2} = {{n+1} \choose 3}-{n \choose 3}
{n\choose 1} = {{n+1} \choose 2} - {n\choose 2}
P(n) - P(n-1) = Q(n) - Q(n-1)
Q(n) = 2{{n+1} \choose 3} + {{n+1} \choose 2} 
P(0) = 1
Q(0) = 0
P(n) = Q(n) +1 = 2{{n+1} \choose 3} + {{n+1} \choose 2} + 1
n
\frac{(n-\frac{1}{2})\cdot n\cdot (n+\frac{1}{2})}{3} + 1
